# Cloudflare Pages headers.
#
# HTML: no-cache so returning visitors always get the newest copy.
# Sprint 28 (Mike 2026-04-24: "why is it that my browser won't pick up
# the latest i always have to do a hard refresh") — previous value was
# `public, max-age=0, must-revalidate`. That looks right on paper but
# without an ETag or Last-Modified validator, `must-revalidate` has
# nothing to validate against; browsers fall back to heuristic caching
# and the in-memory cache still serves old HTML on same-tab reloads.
# `no-cache` is unambiguous: store the response but REVALIDATE with
# origin before every reuse. Works cleanly without validator headers.
# Bundled JS/CSS still have content-hashed filenames + immutable cache.
#
# Long-cache the OG image. iMessage's LinkPresentation will occasionally
# fail to show a preview if the image response has ambiguous caching.
# Making it immutable + public means every unfurl consumer can cache the
# same bytes indefinitely; we bust by changing the filename when the
# asset actually changes.

/*
  Cache-Control: public, no-cache
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN

# ═════ AGENT JSON SURFACES ═════
# All machine-readable endpoints are CORS-open so agents fetching from
# cross-origin contexts (orchestrators on different domains, embeddings
# in third-party tools) can read them directly. Edge cache 5 min, browser
# cache 1 min for most; longer for more-static surfaces.

/agents.json
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, OPTIONS
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=60, s-maxage=300

